              "question": "How might groupthink have affected the disastrous decision to risk the fate of the space shuttle \n\u003ci\u003eColumbia\u003c/i\u003e in 2003?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Engineers who disagreed were asked to leave the discussions, creating strong in-group loyalties."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "NASA officials made the decision to ignore engineers’ warnings based on relative terms, rather than absolute terms, leading to poor decision-making."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "NASA officials disregarded engineers’ warnings, convinced that a loose piece of foam could not harm the shuttle."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Even though many officials disagreed with the decision, they obeyed orders from the White House to carry on."
